results.name: Number of partitions of n^2 into parts greater than n.
maple: a := proc (n) local G, Gser: G := 1/(product(1-x^j, j = n+1 .. n^2)): Gser := series(G, x = 0, n^2+5): coeff(Gser, x, n^2) end proc: 1, seq(a(n), n = 1 .. 27); # _Emeric Deutsch_, Jun 22 2009
mathematica: a[n_] := a[n] = 1/Product[1 - x^j, {j, n + 1, n^2}] + O[x]^(n^2 + 1) // CoefficientList[#, x]& // Last;
Table[Print["a(", n, ") = ", a[n]]; a[n], {n, 0, 28}] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, May 18 2017, adapted from Maple *)
results.author: _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Jun 10 2009
